English for Interviews is the perfect way to practice your interview and interview response skills. Focusing on listening, speaking, and reading, English for Interviews provides wonderful lessons for any students who want to improve their interview skills in English. English for Interviews follows the story of Henry, student from Asia seeking to attend university in the USA. Students follow as he moves through a series of interviews to reach, study, and live in his new country. Based on actual experiences that students traveling overseas may have, English for Interviews brings a level of realism that will help students feel more assured and confident about studying overseas. Even if a student's goals are not to study overseas, English for Interviews will help prepare the student for any formal series of questions and answers held in the English language.Interesting Characters and StorylineRealistic Scenarios that Exchange Students may encounterActivities Arranged for Reading, Writing, Listening and SpeakingVocabulary and Idiom PracticeInteractive Audio CDsHelpful Appendixes to Assist in Studying
